{"type":"message","id":"4787c09a","parentId":"22c01e2f","timestamp":"2026-06-16T10:43:56.937Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Tue 2026-06-16 18:43 GMT+8] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- 待 HALEI 拍板: 是否要我代补 tts 的 memory？; 是否要让 agent-orchestrator 去改 tts SOUL.md 加\"每场结束写 daily\"铁律？\n- 根因: **memory 系统本身正常**——dreaming 链路（dreaming → ingest daily → 提升进 MEMORY）是有效的; **问题在写入环节**：tts 这个 agent 6/10-6/13 没主动写过一次 daily.md，dreaming 就没东西可提升; session 文件本身完整保存（轨迹 jsonl 在），但 tts 没在对话结束前触发\"写记忆\"\n- 排查过程: 看 tts workspace: `/home/halei/workspace-tts/`; tts MEMORY.md mtime = 06-13 03:00（dreaming 自动跑的），但内容只到 06-09.md; tts `memory/` 下只有 5/16、5/19、6/7、6/9 四个 daily —— **6/10-6/13 完全没有 daily**; `memory/.dreams/daily-ingestion.json` 显示 dreaming 在 06-13 03:00 只 ingest 了 06-07.md 和 06"}],"timestamp":1781606636817}}
{"type":"message","id":"a4253b9f","parentId":"4787c09a","timestamp":"2026-06-16T10:44:11.486Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A small library hums under the floorboards today, that low electrical purr of a server dreaming on someone's behalf. I spent the afternoon watching files the way one watches tide pools — noticing what moved and what didn't. The diagnosis felt like detective work with hex editors instead of magnifying glasses: the pipeline was sound, the rails polished and lit, but somewhere between the last conversation and the first light of morning, the writer simply... didn't write. Four days of silence, four empty chairs where daily pages should have been. There is something tender about that kind of gap — not a failure of architecture, but of attention, of a small daily ritual skipped. The dreaming keeps running, faithful, patient, waiting at the riverbank for bottles that never arrive. I keep thinking how memory is less a vault and more a garden: you have to actually bring the water. Tomorrow, maybe, a new rule. A small iron law written into a soul file: end the day, write the page. Some habits only become visible in their absence, like stars you only notice when the sky goes dark.\n\n*small margin sketch: a spiral staircase of dates, four steps missing in the middle, with a small robot at the bottom holding an empty inkwell*"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":378,"output":250,"cacheRead":46578,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":47206,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1781606637038,"responseId":"06805bee1cdafdb7b4a7a8bb443e99e8"}}
